This topic falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the characterization of sequential transducers computable in some circuit complexity classes, which relates to computational complexity (cs.CC) and possibly logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the continuity properties of regular languages, which could also be relevant to the study of semigroups and automata (cs.SC).
